gotiated and discussed.     Share         Leaving the EU: Cross-border Trade      The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     Carol Monaghan (Glasgow North West) (SNP)       Share       3. What recent discussions she has had with the Irish Government on cross-border trade after the UK leaves the EU.  [904411]     Share          The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     Gavin Newlands (Paisley and Renfrewshire North) (SNP)       Share       5. What recent discussions she has had with the Irish Government on cross-border trade after the UK leaves the EU.  [904413]     Share          The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     Peter Grant (Glenrothes) (SNP)       Share       6. What recent discussions she has had with the Irish Government on cross-border trade after the UK leaves the EU.  [904414]     Share          The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     Tommy Sheppard (Edinburgh East) (SNP)       Share       7. What recent discussions she has had with the Irish Government on cross-border trade after the UK leaves the EU.  [904415]     Share          The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     The Secretary of State for Northern Ireland (Karen Bradley)       Share       I have regular conversations with the Irish Government. We both recognise the importance of the trade that takes place across the island of Ireland, which is worth £4 billion to the Northern Ireland economy. Equally, Great Britain markets are fundamental to Northern Ireland, with sales worth some £14.6 billion.