pean Union, in Northern Ireland as in the rest of the United Kingdom we will use the opportunity to enhance animal welfare standards?     Share          The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     Mr Vara       Share       My hon. Friend makes a good point. The Government share the public’s high regard for animal welfare, and we are proud to have some of the highest animal welfare standards in the world. He will appreciate, however, that animal welfare is a devolved matter in Northern Ireland, and it would be for a future Northern Ireland Executive to determine their own policy. We have been clear that when we leave the EU, we will not only maintain the existing rules on animal welfare but, where possible, look to strengthen those requirements.     Share                    The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     Sir Jeffrey M. Donaldson (Lagan Valley) (DUP)       Share       As the Minister has said, Northern Ireland has very high animal welfare standards, and surely we can do better than what the EU offers in terms of animal welfare standards.     Share          The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     Mr Vara       Share       It is our intention not only to stay at the same level but to continue to improve our levels of animal welfare.     Share                   ×   Suggest Correction            Your Details:         Enter your suggested correction:   0 /1000          Please prove you are not a robot.        Close  Submit               A-Z index | Glossary | Contact us | Freedom of Information | Data Protection |  Jobs | Using this website |  Copyright     © Parliamentary Copyright                     Cookies: We use cookies to give you the best possible experienc